    "Following a detailed review of the full text articles, an additional 5 studies were eliminated, and finally, 42 studies that met the inclusion criteria were considered suitable for qualitative analysis.",
    "A list of the excluded full text articles along with their justifications is presented in Supplementary Appendix 2.",
    "There was excellent inter-reviewer agreement for the study selection process, with Cohen's κ values of 0.89.",
    "The demographic and methodological characteristics of all the included studies are summarized in Tables 2 and 3.",
    "Between 2005 and 2023, a total of 42 studies were identified, focusing on estimating the mid-sagittal plane in patients with facial asymmetry."
